Hello everbody <#CBA9UA4EN|javascript>! My name is Filipe Alves and I'm new to the community and to HubSpot.
I have a doubt and if you can help me.

I want to get the title of the blog page ( {{ page_meta.name }} ) and pass it to a variable in javascript to perform a function, can you tell me how to do this? Follow my code below:

```             &lt;h1 id="new"&gt;&lt;/h1&gt; 
               {% require_js %}
                &lt;script&gt;
                  var phrase= {{page_meta.name}} ; //the sentence in question

                  var separate_phrase = phrase.split(' '); //divide into parts
                  var last_phrase = separate_phrase.pop(); // remove the last part with pop and save it in a variable

                  var first_words = eparate_phrase.join(' '); //create a space-separated string(' ') with the remaining parts
                  var result= `${first_words }, ${last_phrase} `; //resultado

                  var tag = document.createElement("span");

                  tag.append(last_phrase);


                  var element1 = document.getElementById("new");
                  var element2 = document.getElementById("new");

                  element2.append(first_words);
                  element1.append(' ', tag);

                &lt;/script&gt;
               {% end_require_js %}
              ```
The idea is to separate the sentence and take the last word and put it inside a &lt;span&gt; tag.
